# Installing Ollama

Ollama is an open-source AI framework that provides a simple way to run large language models locally. To install Ollama, you can use one of the following methods:

## Using the CLI (Recommended)
Install Ollama via curl:
```bash
curl -L https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
```
For Windows users, download and run the installer from [Ollama's official website](https://ollama.com).

## Using Binary Packages
Download the appropriate binary package for your OS from the [GitHub releases page](https://github.com/ollamalang/ollama/releases) and follow the installation instructions provided.

## Docker
If you prefer using Docker, you can pull the Ollama image:
```bash
docker pull ollamalang/ollama
```


After installation, ensure Ollama is accessible in your PATH. You can verify the installation by running `ollama --version`.

Once installed, you'll be ready to use Ollama as the backend for image assertions in Playwright.
